  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Together, these results suggest that performance of our model is good across datasets when punctuation is present in narratives.",
    "We expected performance to be worse on the two tasks scored with different guidelines, because the model was not trained to mimic those guidelines.",
    "Indeed, performance was comparatively poor on the thoughts task, in which participants provided the thoughts that came to mind as they looked at a picture, and also on the related picture description task.",
    "These results suggest that our automated scoring procedure should not be used, or used with caution, on tasks that are not optimized for scoring with the interview (Levine et al., 2002) or the adapted interview (e.g., Addis et al., 2008).",
    "Our model will likely perform best when used with data that are similar to our training data, i.e., when scoring internal and external data from future simulation and autobiographical memory tasks."
  ],
